.TH MAKNOON 1 "April 2026" "3.0.0" "Maknoon Manual"
.SH NAME
maknoon \- High-performance, Post-Quantum CLI encryption tool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maknoon
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Maknoon (مكنون) is an industrial-grade encryption tool designed for a post-quantum world. 
It implements a stateful **Engine** architecture (v3.0) utilizing NIST-standard ML-KEM (Kyber1024) for asymmetric encryption, ML-DSA (Dilithium87) for digital signatures, and XChaCha20-Poly1305 for streaming data integrity.
.PP
The tool features a modular **Profile** system for cryptographic agility, multi-core parallelism, and a capability-based **Agent Sandbox** for secure execution by AI agents. All data is processed in 64KB chunks to ensure a constant memory footprint.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Core Commands
.TP
.B encrypt [file/dir]
Encrypt a file or directory. Directories are automatically archived (TAR).
Supports \-\-public-key for asymmetric mode and \-\-passphrase for symmetric mode.
.TP
.B decrypt [file]
Decrypt and restore data. Automatically detects encryption type, compression, and archiving.
Use \-\-overwrite to bypass safety checks.
.TP
.B send [file/dir]
Send data via secure ephemeral P2P transport (Magic Wormhole).
.TP
.B receive [code]
Receive data from a peer using a Wormhole code.
.TP
.B chat [code]
Start a secure, ephemeral Ghost Chat session. Supports TUI and JSONL (for agents).
.TP
.B info [file]
Displays detailed cryptographic metadata of an encrypted Maknoon file.
.SS Identity Management
.TP
.B keygen
Generate a full Post-Quantum identity (KEM + SIG + Nostr keys).
Protected by Argon2id and optionally hardware-backed via FIDO2 (\-\-fido2).
.TP
.B identity [subcommand]
.RS
.TP
.B active
List absolute paths of available public keys for encryption.
.TP
.B publish [handle]
Anchor an identity to a global registry (Nostr, DNS, or deSEC).
.TP
.B info [name]
Show details about a local identity and its filesystem paths.
.TP
.B rename [old] [new]
Rename a local identity and its associated key files.
.TP
.B split [name]
Shard an identity private key using Shamir's Secret Sharing (SSS).
.TP
.B combine [shards...]
Recover an identity from mnemonic shards.
.RE
.TP
.B contact [subcommand]
Manage trusted Petnames (address book).
.RS
.TP
.B add [petname]
Add a new trusted contact with their public keys.
.TP
.B list
List all stored contacts and petnames.
.TP
.B remove [petname]
Delete a contact from the local registry.
.RE
.SS Security & Integrity
.TP
.B sign [file]
Generate a detached ML-DSA-87 signature for a file.
.TP
.B verify [file]
Verify a file's integrity and origin using an ML-DSA public key.
.SS Utilities & Secrets
.TP
.B vault [subcommand]
Manage an encrypted password database (bbolt).
.RS
.TP
.B set [service]
Store a secret (username, password, notes).
.TP
.B get [service]
Retrieve a secret from the vault.
.TP
.B list
List all services stored in the vault.
.TP
.B delete [service]
Permanently remove a secret.
.TP
.B split
Shard the vault's master access key into mnemonics.
.TP
.B recover [shards...]
Reconstruct a vault using mnemonic shards.
.RE
.TP
.B gen [subcommand]
Generate high-entropy secure credentials.
.RS
.TP
.B passphrase
Generate a mnemonic passphrase. Supports \-\-words and \-\-separator.
.TP
.B password
Generate a random character password. Supports \-\-length and \-\-no-symbols.
.RE
.TP
.B config [subcommand]
.RS
.TP
.B list
List all active configuration settings (relays, limits, paths).
.TP
.B set [key] [value]
Update a configuration setting (e.g., security.time, agent.max_workers).
.TP
.B init
Initialize the default configuration file (~/.maknoon/config.json).
.RE
.TP
.B profiles [subcommand]
Manage cryptographic agility profiles.
.RS
.TP
.B list
List built-in (nist, aes, conservative) and custom profiles.
.TP
.B gen <name>
Generate a randomized, validated custom profile.
.TP
.B rm <name>
Remove a custom profile from the configuration.
.RE
.TP
.B schema
Output the complete JSON Schema of all commands for AI Agent consumption.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-public-key
Path to a recipient's public key (.kem.pub). Supports multiple keys.
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-private-key
Path to your private key (.kem.key or .sig.key).
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-passphrase
Passphrase for symmetric operations or unlocking keys.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-compress
Enable Zstd compression.
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-concurrency
Number of parallel workers (0 for auto-scale).
.TP
.B \-\-stealth
Headerless mode; makes ciphertext indistinguishable from random noise.
.TP
.B \-\-shred
Securely delete the original file after successful encryption.
.TP
.B \-\-trust-on-first-use (tofu)
Automatically trust and save unknown public keys encountered during decryption.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Enable strict JSON output on stdout and errors on stderr.
.TP
.B \-\-fido2
Use a hardware security key for KDF and authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-profile [id/name]
Select a specific cryptographic profile.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MAKNOON_PASSPHRASE
Used to unlock keys and vaults non-interactively.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_AGENT_MODE
Set to "1" to enable the restricted Agent Sandbox.
.TP
.B MAKNOON_JSON
Set to "1" to force JSON output mode globally.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/config.json
Global configuration and custom profiles.
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/keys/
Default identity storage.
.TP
.I ~/.maknoon/contacts.db
Trusted contacts and petnames database.
